The paper discusses the design and mitigation of botnets that use privacy infrastructures for cyber attacks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of self-healing network maintenance schemes, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS). The discussion of the resilience and robustness of the botnets falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of these botnets on privacy infrastructure, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CY).
